n%20what%20makes%20applicants%20stand%20out.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20one%20way%20he%20says%20companies%20are%20failing%20to%20properly%20use%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAppian%20CEO%20Matt%20Calkins%20said%20many%20companies%20are%20deploying%20AI%20incorrectly.%20It%20starts%20with%20something%20as%20simple%20as%20reviewing%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20trying%20to%20be%20all%20modern%20and%20everything%2C%20but%20the%20reason%20I%20don't%20like%20that%20is%20we're%20trying%20to%20hire%20at%20a%20very%20elite%20level%2C%20and%20I%20think%20if%20we%20use%20AI%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20start%20checkboxing%2C%26quot%3B%20Calkins%20told%20Business%20Insider%20during%20a%20recent%20dinner%20with%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-process-ai-paper-resumes-in-person-job-interviews-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eupended%20job%20hunting%20and%20hiring.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20major%20companies%20like%20Google%20and%20Salesforce%20told%20Business%20Insider%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20they%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-salesforce-jobs-how-ai-evaluates-resumes-cover-letters-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20use%20AI%20to%20assist%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20reviewing%20candidates%2C%20many%20still%20rely%20entirely%20on%20recruiters%20for%20filtering%20applications.%20Companies%20have%20said%20that%20using%20AI%20to%20help%20with%20the%20influx%20of%20initial%20applications%2C%20ideally%20freeing%20up%20recruiters%20to%20focus%20on%20top%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20found%20that%20some%20applicants%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-process-ai-paper-resumes-in-person-job-interviews-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egoing%20back%20to%20paper%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20try%20to%20cut%20through%20the%20mountain%20of%20applications.%20Some%20hiring%20managers%20are%20returning%20to%20in-person%20interviews%2C%20craving%20more%20direct%20interaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalkins%20said%20he%20fears%20that%20if%20Appian%20relied%20on%20AI%20to%20whittle%20down%20applications%2C%20they%20could%20miss%20out%20on%20a%20potentially%20special%20hire.%20Founded%20in%201999%2C%20Appian%20is%20a%20cloud%20computing%20and%20enterprise%20software%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20supposed%20to%20be%20better%20than%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20supposed%20to%20spot%20the%20magic%20in%20people%20when%20we%20read%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20and%20it%20didn't%20take%20AI%20to%20screen%20for%2C%20I%20don't%20know%2C%20did%20you%20do%20well%20in%20school%20or%20something%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22446ba30c-a161-4402-8889-acf742bd93d2%5C%22%3E'They're%20off%20doing%20silly%20things%20that%20aren't%20going%20to%20matter.'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20on%20the%20hiring%20end%20where%20companies%20are%20missing%20out%2C%20Calkins%20said.%20He%20pointed%20to%20an%20MIT%20study%2C%20which%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-ai-bubble-meta-sam-altman-mit-report-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E95%25%20of%20companies%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehave%20yet%20to%20see%20a%20return%20on%20their%20investment%20in%20generative%20AI.%20Calkins%20said%20it's%20incredible%20to%20see%20%26quot%3Bthe%20technology%20of%20the%20century%26quot%3B%20deployed%20so%20poorly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20happening%20because%20we're%20so%20ignorant%20about%20how%20to%20actually%20put%20AI%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20so%20hard%2C%20you%20need%20to%20connect%20AI%20to%20real%20work.%20Instead%20of%20having%20it%20do%20side%20jobs%2C%20you%20need%20to%20connect%20it%20to%20the%20big%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalkins%20said%20AI%20would%20be%20much%20better%20deployed%20by%20addressing%20the%20massive%20challenges%20that%20large%20companies%20face.%20One%20such%20problem%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20how%20corporations%20are%20%26quot%3Bjust%20inundated%26quot%3B%20with%20all%20kinds%20of%20communication%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20corporations%20get%20a%20million%20pieces%20of%20incoming%20communication%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20some%20are%20on%20paper%2C%20and%20some%20are%20on%20fax%20machines%2C%20and%20some%20are%20on%20emails%2C%20and%20some%20are%20texts%2C%20and%20some%20are%20calls%20that%20are%20transcribed.%20And%20they're%20on%20all%20different%20topics%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAppian%20has%20had%20great%20success%20addressing%20this%2C%20Calkins%20said%2C%20saying%20their%20AI%20can%20understand%20everything%20from%20emails%20to%20handwritten%20notes%2C%20route%20the%20job%2C%20and%20then%20upload%20it%20to%20the%20correct%20database%20with%2099%25%20accuracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20amazing%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20boring.%20It's%20back%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNobody%20will%20understand%20it%20if%20you%20do%20a%20Super%20Bowl%20ad%20about%20it.%20And%20so%2C%20the%20world%20is%20just%20more%20or%20less%20unaware%20of%20the%20real%20answer%20for%20how%20to%20use%20AI%2C%20and%20they're%20off%20doing%20silly%20things%20that%20aren't%20going%20to%20matter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fappian-ceo-ai-resumes-companies-deployment-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1762250941000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6909260a599d46a4ccc160c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fappian-ceo-ai-resumes-companies-deployment-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Appian%20CEO%20Matt%20Calkins%20said%20that%20he%20doesn't%20trust%20AI%20to%20do%20many%20tasks%2C%20including%20screening%20r%C