ial%20program%20less%20than%20a%20year%20ago%20with%20eight%20vetted%20troops%20who%20already%20command%20attention%20on%20TikTok%2C%20Instagram%2C%20and%20YouTube.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20is%20a%20female%20bodybuilder.%20Another%20is%20a%20public%20affairs%20officer%20who%20preaches%20resilience.%20Some%20merge%20the%20latest%20social%20media%20trends%20with%20military%20peculiarities.%20The%20trial%20run's%20most%20popular%20influencer%20is%20a%20National%20Guard%20soldier%20who%20jokes%20about%20dad%20life%20as%20a%20farmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20realized%20there%20were%20just%20pockets%20we%20could%20not%20pay%20to%20get%20into%2C%26quot%3B%20Col.%20Kris%20Saling%2C%20who%20oversees%20experimentation%20and%20innovation%20in%20Army%20talent%20management%2C%20said%20of%20their%20reach%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20installment%20of%20a%20three-part%20series%20on%20the%20rise%20of%20military%20influencers.%20If%20you%20are%20serving%20or%20have%20served%20and%20want%20to%20share%20your%20experience%20with%20social%20media%20and%20the%20military%2C%20contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20kbaker%40insider.com%20or%20on%20Signal%20at%20kelseybaker75.75.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20first%20installment%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoldier-side-hustle-tiktok-instagram-influencer-pay-army-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThis%20soldier%20built%20a%20side%20hustle%20on%20TikTok%20and%20Instagram%20and%20says%20it's%20now%20paying%20better%20than%20the%20Army%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trial%20program%20aims%20to%20spark%20interest%20in%20enlistment%20among%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-loves-snapchat-instagram-and-youtube-social-media-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyoung%20people%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20service%20doesn't%20pay%20fees%20to%20these%20influencers%20for%20their%20posts%2C%20but%20it%20spent%20about%20%2422%2C000%20on%20their%20travel%20and%20lodging%20around%20a%20marquee%20event%20in%20June.%20(The%20strategy%20worked%2C%20with%20their%20event-related%20posts%20reaching%20an%20impressive%2040%20million%20people%20online%2C%20internal%20documents%20show).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Austin%20von%20Letkemann%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690908950be9845f2dc59c0f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EData%20on%20how%20influencers%20could%20be%20affecting%20recruiting%20is%20almost%20nonexistent%2C%20but%20there%20are%20some%20early%20indications%20that%20this%20could%20be%20a%20real%20opportunity.%3Cp%3EBill%20McCullough%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20service%20has%20wavered%20on%20fully%20embracing%20the%20program%2C%20recently%20pausing%20it%20for%20an%20ethics%20review.%20But%20as%20Secretary%20of%20Defense%20Pete%20Hegseth's%20Recruitment%20Task%20Force%20aims%20to%20find%20%26quot%3Binnovative%20strategies%26quot%3B%20to%20boost%20interest%20in%20military%20service%2C%20there's%20growing%20recognition%20that%20these%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-soldier-went-viral-tiktok-mocking-gen-z-military-influencer-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esoldiers-turned-influencers%3C%2Fa%3E%20connect%20with%20young%20people%20in%20ways%20traditional%20campaigns%20can't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20accounts%20are%20wildly%20popular%20with%20civilians%20and%20troops%20alike%2C%20delivering%20entertainment%20ranging%20from%20wholesome%20family%20content%20to%20cheeky%20irreverence.%20Many%20of%20these%20soldiers%20post%20from%20home%20or%20the%20gym%2C%20like%20any%20other%20influencer.%20Some%20appear%20in%20uniform%2C%20raising%20the%20stakes%20for%20the%20Army%20by%20tying%20its%20brand%20to%20unofficial%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20relatable%2C%20they're%20people%2C%20they're%20human%2C%26quot%3B%20Saling%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20not%20the%20highly%20paid%20actor%20who's%20speaking%20on%20our%20behalf%20and%20probably%20has%20never%20served.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a5bcf00a-aada-4c70-90bf-86e4c54801e9%5C%22%3EThe%20target%20audience%20for%20Army%20influencers%20is%20often%20civilians%20and%20junior%20troops%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20most%20visible%20of%20the%20Army's%20eight%20influencers%20is%20Austin%20von%20Letkemann%2C%20who%20goes%20by%20the%20handle%20%26quot%3Bmandatoryfunday%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20wry%20reference%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bfun%26quot%3B%20unit%20events%20that%20troops%20must%20attend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20typical%20posts%20might%20ponder%20the%20absurdities%20of%20military%20punishment%20and%20logic%2C%20or%20react%20to%20videos%20of%20people's%20poor%20judgment.%20Sometimes%20he's%20on%20base%20at%20Fort%20Hood%2C%20Texas%2C%20where%20he%20occasionally%20collaborates%20with%20two%20other%20influencers%20%E2%80%94%20Sgt.%201st%20Class%20Johnny%20Vargas%2C%20who%20goes%20by%20viva_la_vargas%2C%20and%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Roksolana%20Savyuk%2C%20known%20as%20quuen_baby.%20Last%20year%2C%20von%20Letkemann%20went%20viral%20for%20confronting%20observers%20who%20felt%20%26quot%3Bsorry%26quot%3B%20that%20he%20was%20a%20father%20to%20four%20girls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20show%20people%20that%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnavy-flattop-sails-the-pacific-with-captain-america-battle-flag-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECaptain%20America%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20join%20the%20United%20States%20military%2C%26quot%3B%20von%20Letkemann%20said%20in%20an%20interview.%20In%20many%20videos%2C%20he%20looks%20like%20any%20ordinary%20civilian%20lounging%20at%20home%2C%20excluding%20flashes%20of%20gallows%20humor%20common%20among%20troops%2C%20such%20as%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3Blive%2C%20laugh%2C%20lobotomize%20me%26quot%3B%20displayed%20on%20the%20t-shirts%20and%20mugs%20he%20sells.%20Some%20videos%20touch%20on%20mental%20health%20issues%20or%20cultural%20challenges%20within%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnown%20for%20his%20deadpan%20delivery%2C%20von%20Letkemann%2C%20an%20enlisted%20soldier-turned-junior%20officer%2C%20has%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eamassed%20more%20than%203.5%20million%20followers%20across%20social%20media%20platforms.%20The%20Army's%20ability%20to%20communicate%20with%20two%20of%20its%20most%20important%20populations%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-american-army-soldiers-complain-food-pay-tiktok-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyoung%20civilians%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20might%20become%20recruits%20and%20the%20junior%20troops%20the%20military%20works%20to%20retain%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20national%20security%20and%20an%20organizational%20gap%20influencers%20can%20help%20fill%2C%20he%20said.%20He%20fits%20that%20bill%20with%20a%20soft%20edge%2C%20ridiculing%20the%20oddities%20of%20military%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Austin%20von%20Letkemann%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69090759599d46a4ccc15c16%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Army's%20eight%20influencers%20helped%20the%20service%20rack%20up%20millions%20of%20views%20during%20the%20service's%20birthday%20parade%20this%20summer.%3Cp%3EBill%20McCullough%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20today's%20quasi-peacetime%20military%2C%20young%20service%20members%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20spend%20time%20entering%20data%2C%20navigating%20bureaucracy%2C%20or%20waiting%20for%20orders%20in%20a%20culture%20of%20hurry-up-and-wait%2C%20versus%20charging%20into%20a%20battlefield%20assault.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHighlighting%20such%20frustrations%20doesn't%20diminish%20service%3B%20rather%2C%20it%20pulls%20back%20the%20curtain%20to%20help%20set%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-battlefield-us-soldier-viral-video-hate-comments-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erealistic%20expectations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20His%20inbox%20is%20often%20filled%20with%20messages%20from%20potential%20recruits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20junior%20soldier%2C%20Specialist%20Dylan%20Ogle%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he'd%20previously%20abandoned%20the%20idea%20of%20joining%20the%20Navy%20because%20of%20a%20medical%20issue.%20But%20a%20video%20from%20von%20Letkemann%20pushed%20him%20to%20try%20again%20%E2%80%94%20with%20the%20Army.%20In%20a%202024%20Instagram%20message%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Ogle%20told%20von%20Letkemann%20he%20%26quot%3Binspired%26quot%3B%20him%20to%20join%20and%20%26quot%3Bchanged%20my%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20handful%20of%20his%20posts%20have%20drawn%20criticism%20from%20leaders%20for%20off-color%20content%2C%20he%20said.%20But%20only%20rarely%20%E2%80%94%20after%20all%2C%20it's%20that%20brazen%20irreverence%20and%20satire%20that%20resonate%20with%20troops%20and%20the%20public%20the%20most%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220ed79b29-2f26-489b-95c1-59a9a83abb4d%5C%22%3EContent%20creators'%20reach%20outpaces%20traditional%20Army%20advertising%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20trial%20program%2C%20the%20service%20gathered%20influencers%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20in%20June%20to%20help%20drive%20awareness%20around%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-military-parade-us-army-photos-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EArmy's%20250th%20birthday%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20for%20the%20creators'%20lodging%20and%20travel%20was%20about%20%2422%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20a%20post-parade%20communications%20analysis%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOver%20five%20days%2C%20content%20from%20eight%20influencers%20garnered%20views%20from%20more%20than%2040%20million%20people%20and%20nearly%202%20million%20engagements%20(comments%20and%20reactions)%2C%20the%20analysis%20showed.%20That's%20a%20reach%20that%20traditional%20Army%20advertising%20rarely%20achieves%2C%20outside%20the%20largest%20and%20most%20expensive%20spots%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-famous-super-bowl-commercials%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESuper%20Bowl%20ads%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20parade%2C%20Army%20social%20media%20numbers%20%26quot%3Bincreased%20by%2072%2C000%20followers%20across%20all%20platforms%20(3x%20greater%20than%20average)%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20internal%20analysis%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20there%20were%20265%2C000%20visits%20to%20the%20Army%20Birthday's%20website%20because%20of%20their%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Army-sanctioned%20influencers%20are%20connecting%20with%20young%20people%20in%20new%20ways%2C%20it's%20still%20too%20early%20to%20measure%20their%20impact%20on%20total%20recruiting%2C%20officials%20said.%20Housing%20talent%20like%20von%20Letkemann%20means%20the%20Army%20doesn't%20have%20to%20pay%20nonmilitary%20influencers%20for%20coverage%2C%20which%20can%20cost%20anywhere%20from%20%2415%2C000%20to%20%2475%2C000%20per%20post%2C%20Saling%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20campaign%2C%20however%2C%20has%20rankled%20some%20troops%2C%20who%20observed%20influencers%20staying%20in%20hotel%20rooms%20while%20the%20rank-and-file%20slept%20in%20government%20buildings%20%E2%80%94%20a%20contrast%20that%20Saling%20said%20led%20to%20negative%20impressions.%20And%20while%20soldiers%20on%20social%20media%20are%20barred%20from%20explicitly%20endorsing%20products%2C%20many%20profit%20from%20advertising%20revenue%20or%20from%20selling%20personal%20merchandise.%20That%20presents%20an%20ethical%20quandary%20for%20all%20services%2C%20which%20lack%20a%20common%20framework%20for%20name%2C%20image%2C%20and%20likeness%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20complete%20gray%20zone%2C%26quot%3B%20Saling%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20area%20we%20really%20have%20to%20figure%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20rules%2C%20a%20Pentagon%20spokesperson%20referred%20Business%20Insider%20to%20existing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdod-rapid-response-x-account-loves-hegseth-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDoD-level%20social%20media%20guidelines%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20firmest%20guidelines%20cover%20operational%20security%2C%20partisan%20politics%2C%20and%20compliance%20with%20military%20law.%20Crude%20humor%2C%20edgy%20memes%2C%20and%20provocative%20posts%20aren't%20explicitly%20prohibited%20%E2%80%94%20and%20are%20often%20tolerated.%20The%20guidelines%20are%20generally%20left%20to%20unit%20commanders%20to%20interpret%20and%20enforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVon%20Letkemann%20said%20that%20the%20program%20succeeded%20this%20summer%20because%20the%20Army%20allowed%20sanctioned%20influencers%20to%20post%20whatever%20content%20they%20liked%2C%20unmuzzled%20by%20strict%20guidance%20usually%20seen%20in%20military%20communications.%20%26quot%3BThey%20basically%20told%20us%2C%20'Go%20do%20what%20you%20do%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20their%20parade%20prep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20independence%20or%20freedom%20of%20expression%20isn't%20normally%20encouraged%20in%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20have%20somebody%20who%20goes%20out%20and%20posts%20a%20TikTok%20rant%2C%26quot%3B%20Saling%20said.%20But%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20a%20go-for-broke%20mentality%20in%20the%20Army%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20of%20the%20service's%20changing%20attitude%20toward%20influencers.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20behind%2C%20now%20let's%20throw%20a%20Hail%20Mary%20and%20see%20how%20this%20works.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a1d6243d-eb35-4fde-897e-c6a432dace1b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Army%20has%20struggled%20with%20branding%20for%20years%3C%2Fstrong%3E%